Package game.grounds

Class Tree

java.lang.Object
edu.monash.fit2099.engine.positions.Ground
game.grounds.Mature
All Implemented Interfaces:
Capable, Printable, Jumpable, Resettable
public class Tree
extends Ground
implements Jumpable, Resettable
The Tree class is a class that represents the final stage of a tree's life cycle. The Tree class is a subclass of the Ground class and implements the Jumpable and Resettable interfaces.
Since:
02-May-2022
Author:
Connor Gibson, Shang-Fu Tsou, Lucus Choy

    • tick

      public void tick​(Location location)
      Ground can also experience the joy of time. Ran every player turn, increments Tree's age; spawns a new sprout every 5 rounds randomly. Has a 20 percent chance to wither and die every turn If it does not die, it has a 15 percent chance of spawning a Koopa at its location.
      Overrides:
      tick in class Ground
      Parameters:
      location - The location of the Tree
